    The hull is spanned by the lowest energy surface in composition space.
    Materials on the hull are thermodynamically stable against decomposition into competing phases.
    For visual clarity, we show only ground states in this phase diagram.
    Usually, every observed stable phase has many higher-energy experimentally inaccessible polymorphs which would quickly phase-separate into the stable phases if synthesized.
    ML-predicted hull distance $Δ E_d$, a.k.a. $E_"hull dist"$ hereafter, is the central property of interest in many parts of this thesis.
