=== ROC Curves
<sec:roc-curves>

A material is classified as stable if the predicted $E_"above hull"$ is below the stability threshold which we set to $t_"stab" = #si0[0eV/atom]$ hull distance.
To test the sensitivity of different models to this threshold, we plot the receiver operating characteristic (ROC) curve for each model in @fig:roc-models. #mace-mp achieves the highest area under curve (AUC) of 0.91, coming in 1.4x higher than the worst model, the Voronoi Random Forest.

