@fig:parity-highest-phonon-bands-freq compares the highest band frequencies (a.k.a. bandwidth) predicted by ML force fields and DFT.
The bandwidth correlates with the stiffness of the material's strongest bond, making it a physically meaningful quantity in its own right.
All three models demonstrate acceptable agreement with DFT, with #mace-mp ($R^2 = 0.99$, MAE = 1.79) slightly outperforming #chgnet ($R^2 = 0.98$, MAE = 2.31) which in turn beats #m3gnet ($R^2 = 0.94$, MAE = 4.35) by a margin.
The largest discrepancies between PBE and ML bandwidths are shown in @tab:worst-phonon-bandswidths.
#mace-mp's largest error of #si1[13THz] are 27% and 26% lower than #chgnet's #si1[18THz] and #m3gnet's #si1[20THz].

